Clemson University Herbarium

*Galax urceolata*

DIAPENSIACEAE OF SOUTH CAROLINA
Oconee County

*Galax aphylla* L.

Location: On the Foothills trail traveling North from Hwy. 107 about a quarter of a mile up the trail.

Habitat: Found along a slope near the trail in a pine heath community.

Description: Perennial, rhizomatous, evergreen, acaulescent, sub-shrub, leaves glabrous, ovate, serrate margins, petioles 3-25 cm long, raceme inflorescence on a scape, petals white, stamens unite in a corona-like tube, fruit capsule, seeds reddish-brown.

James D. Sexton 11 October 2010
Plant Taxonomy, BIOSC 407
